The "Alles Klappt" Philosophy
We are not rebuilding the CPU; we are extending it. By keeping the design simple—Linear
FSM, fixed SRAM/ROM mapping, and standard-compliant RISC-V—we ensure that this
implementation is verifiable, portable, and above all, sovereign.

This repository serves as the definitive reference. 
Contributions should focus on RTL stability and ISA efficiency.



